!***************************************************************
!Chemical network and cooling/heating for POPSICLE simulations
!Author: Piyush Sharda (Leiden) 2024
!Contact: sharda@strw.leidenuniv.nl
!
!This is a simple one-zone temporal evolution of abundances and temperature over 100 free-fall times for the given density
!***************************************************************
!
!Simply make the test from the KROME home directory via
!>>./krome -test onezone_evolution
!>>cd build
!>>make
!>>./test
!
!The test will output a file called fort.22
!which can be read in your favorite programming language
!to plot stuff
!
!To activate the equilibrium test where density is kept fixed
!and abundances and temperature are evolved to equilibrium
!use the test_eqbm.f90 file. Rename it test.f90 and run the test as above
